.TH characters
.SH DESCRIPTION
Characters are game objects that can move around the area.
.br
Characters can have inventory, skills, trainings, effects, dialogs, quests.
.SH PARAMETERS
.P
* id
.br
Unique ID for the character.
.P
* level
.br
Character level of experience.
.P
* gender
.br
Character gender ID.
.P
* race
.br
Character race ID.
.P
* attitude
.br
Character attitude ID.
.P
* alignment
.br
Character aligment ID.
.SH XML EXAMPLE
.nf
  <character id="charTest1"
	level="18"
	gender="genderMale"
	race="raceHuman"
	attitude="attFriendly"
	alignment="aliLawfulGood">
    <attributes strenght="1"
		constitution="1"
		dexterity="1"
		inteligence="1"
		wisdom="1"/>
    <inventory>
      <item id="iwIronSword"
	    loot="true"/>
      <item id="itemCopperCoin1"
	    amount="10"
	    loot="true"/>
    </inventory>
    <dialogs>
      <dialog id="diaTest1"/>
    </dialogs>
  </character>
